[{"from": "human", "value": "What configuration does Nginx require for LimeSurvey?"}, {"from": "gpt", "value": "If you are running LimeSurvey on the Nginx web server and wish to set the 'urlFormat' to 'path', you need a specific Nginx configuration. An example configuration is as follows:
```nginx
server {
    set $host_path "/PATH/TO/LIMESURVEY";
    server_name YOUR.SERVER.FQDN;
    root /PATH/TO/LIMESURVEY;
    charset utf-8;
    try_files $uri /index.php?$uri&$args;
    location ~ ^/(application|docs|framework|locale|protected|tests|themes/\w+/views) {
        deny  all;
    }
    location ~ ^/tmp/runtime/ {
        deny  all;
    }
    location ~ \.php$ {
        fastcgi_split_path_info  ^(.+\.php)(.*)$;
        try_files $uri index.php;
        fastcgi_pass   127.0.0.1:9000;
        include fastcgi_params;
    }
}
```
This setup ensures that requests are correctly processed by PHP and that access to sensitive directories is restricted."}]
